
                                            The shooting, believed to be gang-related, occurred on Saturday afternoon.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A manhunt is underway in Helenvale in Port Elizabeth following the fatal shooting of a two-year-old boy. The shooting, believed to be gang-related, occurred on Saturday afternoon. An unknown suspect started shooting at a 17-year-old who was sitting on the steps of a house. The teen ran away, and two-year-old Akiem Baartman was struck in the head while playing in the street. The teen was also shot and wounded in the neck. The police's Priscilla Naidu: "The shooting of the teenager is gang related and we are investigating a case of murder and attempted murder. The suspect has not been arrested and we are looking for him."